  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/212361385-fca1b752-661e-40e0-a7ba-887e809d0640.png\" width=\"400\" />\r\n\r\n1. `A` and `B` are mutual contacts\r\n2. `A` creates a private group chat with `B` as member.\r\n3. `A` removes `B` from the group chat.\r\n4. `B` receives a unread notification saying \"Removed from group chat\".\r\n5. `B` can press on the notification and see the private group chat past messages (the chat is in read-only mode). Once the chat is opened, the notification is automatically marked as `read`.\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\n- `status-go` doesn't currently generate a notification when an owner removes a member from a private group chat.\r\n- The group chat is visible to a group member, even if the owner removed them from the chat. Only when the ex-member intentionally leaves the chat that the group chat is no longer displayed in the `Group chats` list.\r\n\r\n`Figma - Shell for Mobile`: https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=3804%3A812855&t=ANqnR83VEKQqzHRY-0",
